It's no big deal.

03:45.058 --> 03:47.193
What?
You have a boyfriend.

03:47.227 --> 03:48.995
Yeah, but Tommy
goes to church!

03:49.029 --> 03:50.230
Nick is a freak!

03:51.164 --> 03:52.198
So what?

03:52.232 --> 03:53.466
So this...

03:53.499 --> 03:55.468
Freaks only date
freak girls.

03:55.502 --> 03:57.037
And you're not
a freak girl.

03:57.070 --> 03:58.972
How do you know?

03:59.005 --> 04:00.907
'Cause freaks
go all the way.

04:00.941 --> 04:04.511
Millie, you've no idea
what you're talking about.

04:04.545 --> 04:06.479
What about
Patty Filker?

04:06.513 --> 04:09.616
She's a freak girl.
And she has a baby!

04:09.650 --> 04:12.085
But I guess that's
no big deal either.

04:12.118 --> 04:15.922
Millie, mind your
own business, OK?

04:17.758 --> 04:20.126
Hurry up. I don't want
to be late for bio.

04:20.160 --> 04:21.728
Why? What is
the big deal?

04:21.762 --> 04:24.397
Well, yesterday I was
late, and everyone
looked at me.

04:28.001 --> 04:29.369
Hi, Sam.
(LOCKER DOOR SLAMS)

04:29.402 --> 04:31.738
Oh, hi, Cindy.
How are you?

04:32.405 --> 04:35.609
Ho ho, hey,
Merv Griffin!

04:35.642 --> 04:36.777
Nice interview.

04:39.112 --> 04:40.714
Come on back, Lindsay.

04:41.582 --> 04:42.916
Is there
something wrong?

04:42.949 --> 04:45.586
No. Just checkin' in
with my good friend
Lindsay Weir.

04:45.619 --> 04:47.187
Anything wrong with that?

04:47.220 --> 04:48.421
I guess not.

04:48.454 --> 04:50.056
So how's
everything going?

04:50.090 --> 04:51.858
Classes keeping
you interested?

04:51.892 --> 04:53.259
Yeah, sure.

04:53.293 --> 04:56.530
Hey, have you checked
out the new Rush album?

04:56.563 --> 04:58.832
I've gotta say
it rocks pretty heavily,

04:58.865 --> 05:02.102
and that's comin'
from a guy who's
seen Hendrix live.

05:02.135 --> 05:04.104
Yeah, I... I heard
it's pretty good.

05:04.137 --> 05:05.405
So...

05:07.440 --> 05:09.943
I understand that you
and Nick Andapolous

05:09.976 --> 05:11.244
are gettin' pretty tight.

05:11.277 --> 05:12.412
How's that goin'?

05:12.445 --> 05:15.181
Mr. Rosso, Nick and I
are just friends.

05:15.215 --> 05:16.316
That's all.

05:16.349 --> 05:17.984
Hey, no need to explain
anything to me.

05:18.018 --> 05:21.788
I got it on in a van
at Woodstock, so
I'm not judgin' anybody.

05:21.822 --> 05:24.991
I just want you to know
what you're getting
yourself into.

05:25.025 --> 05:28.194
I mean, when you're
a teenager, your emotions
are running high.

05:28.228 --> 05:30.664
And it's easy
to get confused.

05:31.532 --> 05:33.934
I want you...
To have this.

05:37.671 --> 05:39.272
Oh, my God!

05:39.305 --> 05:42.175
Come on! Don't let
the pamphlet freak you out.

05:42.208 --> 05:44.044
There's some good stuff
in there.

05:44.077 --> 05:47.013
I... It's just that you've
got to be careful these days.

05:47.581 --> 05:49.315
Yeah, I know. I know.

05:49.349 --> 05:50.917
Do you?

05:50.951 --> 05:52.352
I thought I knew, too.

05:52.385 --> 05:55.388
Until one night,
I was checkin' out
this discotheque.

05:55.421 --> 05:57.791
The one at the bowling alley
on 15 Mile.

05:57.824 --> 06:00.661
I met this girl.
She seemed really nice.

06:00.694 --> 06:02.996
We danced a bit.
I kissed her.

06:03.029 --> 06:05.398
One thing
led to another and...

06:05.431 --> 06:07.601
Now I get sores on my lip
once a month.

06:10.070 --> 06:11.938
I have herpes.

06:13.640 --> 06:15.241
It doesn't hurt that much,
but believe me,

06:15.275 --> 06:16.610
you don't want it!

06:18.211 --> 06:19.713
Can I please go now?

06:20.847 --> 06:22.583
I just blew your mind,
didn't I?

06:23.483 --> 06:26.753
No! Uh‐uh.
No, I just, um...

06:26.787 --> 06:28.454
I don't want to
be late for lunch.

06:28.488 --> 06:31.057
OK, OK, just use
your head, Lindsay.

06:31.091 --> 06:32.158
That's all I ask.

06:33.026 --> 06:34.060
You got it.

06:46.873 --> 06:50.410
Man! Gordon reeks!

06:50.443 --> 06:52.345
You think he
ever takes a shower?

06:52.378 --> 06:54.615
SAM: Maybe he
takes baths instead.

06:54.648 --> 06:57.250
My mom says that they
don't really get you clean.

06:57.283 --> 06:59.185
Yeah, you just sit
in your own filth.

07:00.253 --> 07:02.222
All right,
let's settle down.

07:02.255 --> 07:04.457
We've got
a lot to do today.

07:04.490 --> 07:06.359
We're going to be
dissecting kittens.

07:06.392 --> 07:07.528
(STUDENTS GASP)

07:07.561 --> 07:09.429
Just trying
to get your attention.

07:09.462 --> 07:11.665
But you will be getting
your lab partners today.

07:11.698 --> 07:12.799
TEACHER: Uh, McKenna?

07:12.833 --> 07:14.000
I hope I get to be
paired up with Cindy.

07:14.034 --> 07:15.268
TEACHER: You get to be
paired up with Boyle.

07:15.301 --> 07:16.336
Hey, what about me?

07:16.369 --> 07:17.938
Please let it be Cindy.

07:17.971 --> 07:18.805
Weir?

07:18.839 --> 07:21.074
Your lab partner
will be Gordon Crisp.

07:23.343 --> 07:26.680
Bill, your partner
will be Cindy Sanders.

07:27.413 --> 07:30.250
Oh, how interesting.

07:30.283 --> 07:32.719
Me and Cindy,
you and Gordon.

07:33.486 --> 07:34.521
Well, I better...

07:34.555 --> 07:36.523
I better go sit next
to my lab partner.

07:39.693 --> 07:42.563
Well, there goes Cindy's
grade point average.

07:42.596 --> 07:44.330
TEACHER: Bob Carr.

07:44.364 --> 07:46.032
Siskin, you'll be working...

07:46.066 --> 07:47.568
Excuse me, madam.

07:48.401 --> 07:49.536
May I take this seat?

07:49.570 --> 07:50.771
Sure, have a seat.

07:54.007 --> 07:55.876
TEACHER: All right,
people, let's go.

07:56.476 --> 07:57.711
Find your lab partner.

07:57.744 --> 07:58.779
Remember, science waits...

07:58.812 --> 08:00.514
Oh, man!
...for no man.

08:14.127 --> 08:15.128
Lindsay?

08:19.332 --> 08:22.268
I think it's really
great that you and
Nick are goin' out.

08:23.937 --> 08:25.672
Yeah. me, too.

08:26.439 --> 08:27.641
No, I mean it.

08:28.675 --> 08:30.010
Nick's a great guy.

08:32.045 --> 08:34.781
I give him a hard time,
but, you know...

08:36.116 --> 08:37.183
He's the man!

08:38.451 --> 08:41.522
I just think it's
really great you
guys are goin' out.

08:46.392 --> 08:48.228
He's a really great guy.

08:51.231 --> 08:53.634
Yeah. I know.

09:03.644 --> 09:07.280
(WHISPERING)
Nick's a stud...
You know?

09:07.313 --> 09:09.315
I mean, he may
not seem like it,

09:09.916 --> 09:11.151
but he is.

09:12.553 --> 09:13.854
Mr. Dizario,

09:13.887 --> 09:15.822
don't you have
something to do?

09:16.823 --> 09:18.659
Right, but I thought
we were going to do that

09:18.692 --> 09:20.326
after class, Miss Yeats.

09:20.360 --> 09:22.629
Ha‐ha. Be still,
my beating heart.

09:29.603 --> 09:31.237
(WHISPERING)
I like that dress.

09:33.640 --> 09:34.775
How come
you're not eating?

09:34.808 --> 09:37.644
